
# There wonâ€™t be much here, but this will just include the DOS version of bash
# aliases, for situations when I need to run a certain command in the Windows
# command prompt.

# Run bash in a Docker container, assuming the container is named
# (your current basename)Instance. Similar to the *sh alias, but here because
# arrow keys and tab completion doesn't seem to work in winpty. See .aliases for
# more.
dbash=for /F %i in ("%cd%") do @set currentdir=%~ni&& call docker start %currentdir%Instance && call docker exec -it %currentdir%Instance bash
